# Production API (required for S3 / CloudFront builds).
# Use your Elastic Beanstalk environment URL from the AWS console (no trailing slash).
# Rebuild frontend after changing this.
#
# VITE_API_ORIGIN=http://your-env.eba-xxxx.eu-west-3.elasticbeanstalk.com
# Or if the load balancer serves HTTPS:
# VITE_API_ORIGIN=https://your-env.eba-xxxx.eu-west-3.elasticbeanstalk.com
#
# Local dev: leave unset; localhost uses http://localhost:3000 from src/lib/api.ts
#
# Optional: URL for “Help documentation” on the Baseline page (opens in a new tab).
# VITE_HELP_DOC_URL=https://example.com/your-help-doc
